itical temperatures for $\\nu = 0$ states should be an\norder of magnitude higher than those for $|\\nu| = 1$ states, consistent with\nthe fact that the low temperature gap for $\\nu = 0$ is roughly an order of\nmagnitude larger than that for $|\\nu| = 1$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Jun 2020 18:31:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 5 Nov 2020 21:22:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-09"}
