mpared to\nthat in the particle-hole channel. We show that $T_{p,0}$ remains finite at\nlarge $N$ due to special properties of fermions with Matsubara frequencies $\\pm\n\\pi T$, but all other $T_{p,n}$ terminate at $N_{cr} = O(1)$. The gap function\nvanishes at $T \\to 0$ for $N > N_{cr}$ and remains finite for $N < N_{cr}$.\nThis is consistent with the $T =0$ analysis.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Jun 2020 15:48:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 3 Aug 2020 15:17:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-08-05"}
